protein.specific_function: DNA helicase that may play a role in the repair of DNA that is damaged by ultraviolet light or other mutagens. Exhibits a magnesium-dependent ATP-dependent DNA-helicase activity that unwinds single- and double-stranded DNA in a 3'-5' direction.

hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides, in phosphorus-containing anhydrides
